    <completed>2026-06-25</completed>
    <completion-notes>Deployed PB-017 sprk_configjson via MCP update_record (whole-doc replace). Pre-deploy state was 1-block stub (schedule + channel only, no nodes/edges). Post-deploy verified all 5 nodes (Start, Lookup My Matters, Query Matter Activity, Has Activity?, Create Notification) and 4 edges. ActionType 52 LookupUserMembership for sprk_matter entity present; QueryDataverse targets Spaarke custom sprk_event with link-entity sprk_matter and membership-scope union (sprk_regardingmatter IN myMatters.ids OR record-owner OR matter-owner = current user); CreateNotification regardingType=sprk_event with deduplication key matter-activity:{userId}:{eventId}:{modifiedon}; statecode=Active preserved. Component Justification: existing=PB-017 stub (no real query); extension=Yes (stub → full promotion of same row); cost-of-doing-nothing=users get zero matter-activity notifications, AC-8 fails by construction. Smoke notes: projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/notes/smoke/024-matter-activity-deploy.md.</completion-notes>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>020, 021</dependencies>
    <blocks>026</blocks>
    <tags>jps, dataverse, deploy</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Promotes stub playbook (PB-017) to full implementation. Independent JSON file — parallel-safe with 022/023/025. Component Justification (CLAUDE.md §11) required because we are materially extending an existing stub into a functioning playbook.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>D</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>Edit `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/notification-matter-activity.json` (PB-017). Replace the stub with a full node graph: Start → `LookupUserMembership(sprk_matter)` → `QueryDataverse` (union of `sprk_matter`, `sprk_project`, `sprk_workassignment` records modified within last 24h where the record's ID is in the membership matter set) → `CreateNotification` (one per modified record). Redeploy via MCP `update_record` on PB-017. Include Component Justification block (was-stub → now-functional).</prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. JPS playbook designer + Dataverse query author (FetchXml multi-entity union).</role>

  <goal>`notification-matter-activity.json` is a fully functional playbook (no longer a stub). Deployed PB-017 row reflects the full graph. `jps-validate` passes. AC-8 satisfied (when a matter the user is a member of is modified within last 24h, an appnotification row appears in this category).</goal>

  <context>
    <background>R4 spec FR-8 (line 145) replaces the PB-017 stub with a working implementation. The stub currently does nothing — users get zero matter-activity notifications. Full graph: LookupUserMembership resolves user's matters, QueryDataverse fetches sprk_matter / sprk_project / sprk_workassignment records modified in last 24h where ID IN membership matters, CreateNotification emits one notification per modified record. Component Justification (CLAUDE.md §11): existing=stub PB-017 (no real query), extension=Yes (promoting stub to functional), cost-of-doing-nothing=users get zero matter-activity notifications.</background>
