  <steps>
    <step order="1">Load knowledge files. Read spec FR-8 + AC-8.</step>
    <step order="2">Read PB-016 reference (`notification-new-documents.json`) and the current stub `notification-matter-activity.json` to understand starting state.</step>
    <step order="3">Author Component Justification block (CLAUDE.md §11): 3-question template with concrete failure mode.</step>
    <step order="4">Design the full node graph: Start → LookupUserMembership(sprk_matter) → QueryDataverse (3 separate sub-queries unioned: sprk_matter modifiedon&gt;=now-24h AND matterid IN membership, sprk_project regarding-matter IN membership AND modifiedon&gt;=now-24h, sprk_workassignment regarding-matter IN membership AND modifiedon&gt;=now-24h) → CreateNotification (one per row).</step>
    <step order="5">Replace stub JSON with full graph. Include Component Justification in JSON top-level metadata.</step>
    <step order="6">Validate via `jps-validate` skill.</step>
    <step order="7">Audit via `jps-playbook-audit` skill against deployed Action codes.</step>
    <step order="8">Redeploy via `mcp__dataverse__update_record` on PB-017 — set `sprk_configjson`.</step>
    <step order="9">Verify deployment via `mcp__dataverse__read_query`.</step>
    <step order="10">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`.</step>
    <step order="11">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: change task 024 status to ✅.</step>
    <step order="12">Document UAT script + Component Justification rationale in `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/notes/`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="mcp-dataverse">update_record — redeploy PB-017 sprk_configjson; read_query — verify; describe — confirm sprk_matter / sprk_project / sprk_workassignment metadata for the FetchXml query author.</tool>
